Nyanga police have pleaded for assistance to track down perpetrators who shot and killed a motorist in an attempted hijacking. Police spokesperson Captain FC van Wyk said the incident took place on November 5 at about 16:10 on the corner of Monwood Drive and Sheffield Road in Browns Farm. Van Wyk said according to reports, the deceased was shot by unknown assailants after he dropped off his employees. "The suspects wanted to hijack his LDV but the owner sped off and the suspects fired shots at the vehicle wounding him. He was rushed to a nearby hospital where he later succumbed due to the injuries sustained," said Van Wyk. This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. WATCH: Armed robbers hijack man, force him to withdraw R19K Police in Johannesburg are on the hunt for three armed men who hijacked a man in Albertville on Tuesday evening. Anyone with any information or who might have witnessed the incident or might know the suspects is kindly requested to contact the police.